76
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:00,750
I was hoping for a lot.

77
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:05,154
I missed your jokes.

78
00:10:07,770 --> 00:10:09,158
You've worked hard.

79
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:12,729
Needle. Needle.

80
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:15,064
The needle. I'm sorry.

81
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,210
What do you have to be sorry for?

82
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,302
I am the one who is sorry.

83
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:24,641
What is the UN's radio code?

84
00:10:47,690 --> 00:10:48,931
I won't do this again.

85
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:56,606
I am believing in this promise again.

86
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:03,579
I was curious since earlier.
What is that?

87
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,816
It is your memorial ritual food.

88
00:11:07,430 --> 00:11:09,018
Today is your death anniversary.

89
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:13,356
As if I haven't done enough, I was preparing for
my boyfriend's death memorial ceremony table...

90
00:11:17,070 --> 00:11:21,064
By chance... you're not, right?

91
00:11:21,464 --> 00:11:22,098
What?

92
00:11:23,010 --> 00:11:23,866
Knock, knock.

93
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:27,070
Hi Beauty, here is your knife.

94
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,605
Can you see that person?

95
00:11:30,050 --> 00:11:32,108
Yeah. He's very handsome. Boyfriend?

96
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:35,745
Thank God. I thought
I was seeing things.

97
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:37,647
-Thank you. Good night.
-Good night.

98
00:11:40,590 --> 00:11:43,386
You killed me twice.

99
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:45,855
Did you just treat me as a ghost,
even though you're a doctor?!

100
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,590
When you studied science?

101
00:11:47,824 --> 00:11:49,659
Who told you to show up on the
anniversary of your death?

102
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:52,320
Whether you are a human or
a ghost, eat the fruits,

103
00:11:52,330 --> 00:11:54,030
since I prepared them for you to eat.

104
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:55,164
Drink the wine as well.

105
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,300
I couldn't bring cheongju,
so it's in place of that.

106
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:00,536
You prepared a lot. Far
away in a foreign land.

107
00:12:04,006 --> 00:12:04,941
Wait a minute.

108
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:12,682
How come you didn't call at all, wench?
I was worried.

109
00:12:12,990 --> 00:12:14,370
I am sorry. I was super busy.

110
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:16,280
-Busy my ass.
-Sunbae!

111
00:12:16,290 --> 00:12:17,930
Dr. Kang!

112
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:19,021
Seriously.

113
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:21,450
Why a video call? It's making me blush.

114
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:24,727
Hey! I can't see that heated
face of yours, so stand over in the light.

115
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:25,962
Okay.

116
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:27,830
Here?

117
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:35,972
I am not the only one seeing, right?

118
00:12:37,450 --> 00:12:40,610
I also see him.

119
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:44,714
Are you okay? You don't see him?

120
00:12:45,114 --> 00:12:45,815
See what?

121
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:51,587
Today is Captain Yoo's
death anniversary, right?

122
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:57,693
Then... That is the memorial
ceremony table, and...

123
00:12:58,070 --> 00:13:01,197
Oh... that's true. He came to eat the
food off of his ceremonial table...

124
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:10,640
Wow, this woman tried to kill
me three times. Is it fun?

125
00:13:10,673 --> 00:13:13,576
You aren't planning to do this kind
of event after coming back alive?

126
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,045
But my team is really cute, right?

127
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:18,748
They must have caught on!

128
00:13:21,230 --> 00:13:25,021
Sunbae, listen to me
carefully from now on.

129
00:13:26,850 --> 00:13:28,191
Please don't ask me for reasons.

130
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:29,292
What is it?

131
00:13:29,525 --> 00:13:30,893
That you love him...

132
00:13:32,190 --> 00:13:33,429
That you missed him...

133
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:36,866
Express it to your heart's content...

134
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:39,836
So that he won't have lingering
attachments to this world.

135
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:41,337
What?

136
00:13:42,340 --> 00:13:43,773
Even though you won't believe it,

137
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:47,443
Captain Yoo is over there.

138
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:51,514
Please tell him to go to a good place.

139
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,151
I can go crazy.

140
00:13:55,384 --> 00:13:57,320
They are telling you to leave
as soon as you got here.

141
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:59,330
If you tell me to leave
already, I will be upset.

142
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:01,520
Wow!

143
00:14:03,110 --> 00:14:04,460
Oh my gosh.

144
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,362
Hello, everyone.

145
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:10,867
Now, this is Captain
Yoo's current state.

146
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:13,669
So you know how happy I will be tonight?

147
00:14:14,030 --> 00:14:16,105
I will explain the
details when I go back.

148
00:14:16,380 --> 00:14:19,242
Stop bothering me for today.
I will hang up. Bye.

149
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:24,150
-It was Captain Yoo, right? Right?
-Right.

150
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,649
-He wasn't a ghost, right?
-I think so.-I'm not seeing things, right?

151
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:39,428
Attention! To our Commander...

152
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:40,897
Thank you.

153
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:45,701
I am really grateful that
you guys came back alive.

154
00:14:51,410 --> 00:14:52,942
Captain Yoo Si Jin.

155
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:56,045
Sergeant First Class Seo Dae Young.

156
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,016
Hey, you punks!

157
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:05,288
When I think about how much I suffered because
of you I don't even want to look at you...

158
00:15:07,530 --> 00:15:10,860
I got promoted to colonel while you two
were gone, but this kind of thin...

159
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,095
Getting promoted a little
sooner than my colleagues...

160
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,450
Team Leader!

161
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:17,180
Having a nice photo of me in interview with The
Korea Defense Daily. Why would they be important?

162
00:15:17,190 --> 00:15:19,790
Team Leader! Team Leader!

163
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:22,530
To me, in the world,
you two are the most...

164
00:15:26,870 --> 00:15:29,011
Ah, seriously!

165
00:15:29,390 --> 00:15:32,315
You're here!

166
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:36,310
Yoo Si Jin and Seo Dae Young will write
reports in place of work for the time being.

167
00:15:36,330 --> 00:15:39,221
The report should be
as thick as the Bible.

168
00:15:40,220 --> 00:15:41,958
-We'll be going.
-Goodbye.

169
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:44,026
Hey.

170
00:15:49,770 --> 00:15:54,136
-What are you doing?
-I'm more scared of A4 than I am of C4.

171
00:15:55,638 --> 00:15:57,406
Look at this sharp corner.

172
00:15:57,620 --> 00:16:00,643
If you get cut... Wow, it hurts a lot.

173
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:05,414
On the wrist of the bastard
that was waterboarding us,

174
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,650
I think there was a tattoo of Spetsnaz.

175
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,218
That was the guy who knifed us.

176
00:16:10,786 --> 00:16:13,456
But it makes us look bad if we
only write about being beat up,

177
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:15,570
so let's say that once a
week we counterattacked

178
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:17,626
and that we attempted
to escape once monthly.

179
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:19,170
Let's try and write it honestly.

180
00:16:19,190 --> 00:16:21,263
We did that "twice" monthly.

181
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:25,901
They won't try to confirm
it with the militia, right?

182
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:28,971
Given our situation, they will
believe anything we write.

183
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:33,542
But the problem is, we need an appropriate
balance between reality and drama.

184
00:16:34,990 --> 00:16:36,712
How about using Rambo as a guideline?

185
00:16:38,850 --> 00:16:40,270
Since it took place
during the Vietnam War,

186
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,851
neither the weapons nor
the details will fit.

187
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:44,053
I'd rather go with the
Bourne series instead.

188
00:16:44,130 --> 00:16:46,255
First Lieutenant Yoon likes Matt Damon.

189
00:16:46,370 --> 00:16:49,325
It is perfect. Then I will leave.

190
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:50,693
Where are you going?

191
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:53,496
You have to write it alone.
If we write it separately,

192
00:16:53,590 --> 00:16:55,464
whether we struck three
times or five times,

193
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,310
these details might not line up.

194
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,001
But why is that "alone," me?

195
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,970
Isn't 1st Lieutenant Yoon in Urk?

196
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:05,107
To the soldier whose girlfriend
isn't in Korea, good luck!

197
00:17:11,660 --> 00:17:14,483
Do you remember dumping me here?

198
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,185
Of course.

199
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:19,520
I may dump you again today.

200
00:17:19,530 --> 00:17:22,792
You are kidding, right?
I've been traumatized.

201
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,026
I'm serious.

202
00:17:27,196 --> 00:17:28,798
That's why I'm asking.

203
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:32,301
In the future, will you also keep doing

204
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,336
the work that has you going
to the department store?

205
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:37,506
I was wondering if it's because
you wish to be a hero.

206
00:17:40,610 --> 00:17:42,678
If the story's hero must die,

207
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,914
there is not one soldier who
would be interested in it.

208
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:46,449
Right?

209
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:50,719
We just protect peace in places
that need their peace protected.

210
00:17:50,860 --> 00:17:53,689
I guess you mean you will keep doing
it even though I object to it?

211
00:17:53,970 --> 00:17:55,157
Will you object?

212
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:56,792
Should I not?

213
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:01,897
Even if this time, you may
never ever come back?

214
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:07,870
Don't get anxious. I won't object.

215
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,473
What's the use in objecting to it?

216
00:18:10,770 --> 00:18:13,943
Even if you're sorry,
you won't give it up.

217
00:18:14,690 --> 00:18:17,813
And I'll resent you, but
end up supporting you.

218
00:18:18,310 --> 00:18:21,016
If I'm going to be that way,
I'd rather keep my peace, too.

219
00:18:22,151 --> 00:18:25,521
Of course, only if my
support brings you peace.

220
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,593
Thank you. And I'm sorry.

221
00:18:31,594 --> 00:18:35,397
I'm sorry that all I can
say is that I'm sorry.

222
00:18:36,770 --> 00:18:39,902
Should we go fishing tomorrow
since you didn't get dumped?

223
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:42,438
It's a form of emotional therapy.

224
00:18:43,610 --> 00:18:46,342
I'm going to put on my charm
so don't be startled, and

225
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:49,712
don't feel bad even if
I act really happy.

226
00:18:51,010 --> 00:18:53,482
Be grateful for meeting
a girlfriend like me.

227
00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:06,896
The view is beautiful and
my heart is at peace.

228
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:10,132
I feel the pain in my heart healing.

229
00:19:13,550 --> 00:19:15,938
For two hours already, nothing's biting.

230
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,607
How is it that we haven't
caught a single fish?

231
00:19:21,911 --> 00:19:24,713
Are you creating new trauma

232
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,050
to overcome the pre-existing trauma?

233
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:28,951
This won't work. At this rate,
I'll become too frustrated.

234
00:19:37,850 --> 00:19:39,395
The arboretum is nearby.

235
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:40,980
I'll change my treatment plan.

236
00:19:40,990 --> 00:19:42,665
Let's go for a walk while
breathing in fresh air.

237
00:19:43,690 --> 00:19:46,202
Do you... know how many
kilometers I march a year?

238
00:19:46,850 --> 00:19:49,004
Oh, there's a monastery, too.
How about a monastery?

239
00:19:49,930 --> 00:19:52,308
Do you know how many months

240
00:19:52,610 --> 00:19:54,577
I was trapped with only crew cut men?

241
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:56,512
Then what do you want to do?

242
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:58,714
Something conventional.

243
00:19:59,650 --> 00:20:02,017
The weather's cold and
the fish aren't biting.

244
00:20:02,580 --> 00:20:05,454
"Do you want to take a
rest?" Things like that.

245
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:08,123
Something like "By coincidence,
there's only one room left."

246
00:20:09,658 --> 00:20:10,780
Don't cross the line.

247
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:13,295
But that means we still will be sharing
a room together then.

248
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:14,120
Of Course.

249
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,632
You said that you won't lie in bed with a man.
That's what you said at the hospital last time.

250
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:17,833
That wasn't me.

251
00:20:18,370 --> 00:20:20,369
She was a year younger than me.

252
00:20:20,620 --> 00:20:21,870
She really doesn't
know much of anything.

253
00:20:21,990 --> 00:20:22,972
Right?

254
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:26,542
I really didn't like that girl.

255
00:20:26,742 --> 00:20:27,776
I caught one.

256
00:20:27,876 --> 00:20:29,945
